author: rhuijben
msg: Following up on r1337118, make the commit harvester use the status walk
(The svn cp wc URL case is still handled as before).
This speeds up a fully recursive svn commit of a working copy to about the
same as an svn status followed by a commit of just the individual items.
(So on NFS this will make a huge difference).
On my ram-drive based test environment this speeds up the test suite 4%,
compared to before r1337118 and further improvement is possible/easy.
(harvest_committables): Call the status walker with depth for the normal
(harvest_status_callback): Filter skipped trees an non-interesting statee.
Disable the recursion in this function for normal commits.
